Description: Calcite canopic jar: Hapy; four columns of incised Hieroglyphic text including the prenomen of Psamtek I; lid affixed to the body.
Curator's comments: The jar formed part of a set with EA 36534, EA 36536 and EA 36539. The source of the group, 'Sm', is noted only on the Birch Slip for EA 36539 [E.S.639], but all four jars are inscribed with the same name and they are listed as a set in the 3-volume MS catalogue of the Sams Collection (AES archive).
